- **Redundant BN-activation ordering**: BatchNorm after ReLU in `block1` (i.e., `ReLU → BN`) violates best practice — reduces regularization effect and harms gradient flow.

==================== Suggestions ====================  
- Replace `block1`’s `ReLU → BN → Dropout` sequence with `BN → ReLU → Dropout` to restore proper normalization semantics and improve gradient stability.  
- Replace the 64-dim bottleneck in `classifier` with `hidden_dim // 2` (i.e., 128) and remove `LayerNorm(64)` — use `nn.BatchNorm1d(128)` before final linear for consistent, trainable stabilization.  
